Barbie Mariposa, (alternate title: Barbie: Mariposa and her Butterfly Fairy Friends), is a 2008 direct to video Barbie film and was released on February 26, 2008.

This film is the latest in a series of computer-animated Barbie films. The series so far has sold over 40 million units and generated 700 million dollars in revenue.[1]

The film features the voice of Kelly Sheridan, who has been voicing the Barbie protagonist in all the CGI Barbie films to date.

As with the previous Barbie films, a line of toys, dolls, and other products were made based on and released slightly ahead of the film.

This film is not a part of the Barbie Fairytopia films, but it has a similar plot.
